		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=24870"><span id=>gfross</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>1 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gfross&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Although Druid Halflings have two advantages over Wood Elf Halflings that I know of (better starting stats for the Druid class and a better place for newbie hunting -- no high level MOBs in the newbie section of Misty Thicket and shops right there so you don't have to zone in order to buy and sell stuff), they have one disadvantage that I heard about:&nbsp;&nbsp;their feet are too large to wear a certain type of magic boots.  Anyway, I chose to be a Wood Elf for three reasons.  First, I like the appearance of female wood elves (I play a female Wood Elf) better than that of female Halflings (no offense, please, you Halflings -- Beauty is in the eye of the beholder).  Second, I didn't want to have to look UP all the time at most of the other characters in the game.  And third, I didn't want to be treated by other players as a "little kid," which I have heard some people who roleplay Halflings or Gnomes complain about.  Hope this helps you in making your decision.  Have fun! ^_^</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
